__data__.text: Claim ID CLM-2024-00789-AUTO was filed on January 15, 2024, by policyholder Sarah Mitchell for her 2022 Honda Accord. A multi-vehicle collision occurred at the intersection of Maple Avenue and 5th Street in Seattle, Washington, on January 15, 2024, at 09:23:45 AM. The incident involved three vehicles and resulted in significant property damage and minor injuries. The total estimated claim value is $47,850.

metadata.involved_parties: Sarah Mitchell, Robert Chen, Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson
Sarah Mitchell, Robert Chen, Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 09:23:45 AM PST, a collision occurred at the intersection of Maple Avenue and 5th Street in Seattle, involving Sarah Mitchell and Robert Chen. Mitchell, traveling northbound at 25 mph with a green signal, was struck by Chen, who entered the intersection at 45 mph after the light turned red. The impact caused severe damage to Mitchell's vehicle and resulted in her reporting neck pain and dizziness. No financial amounts were mentioned in the report.

metadata.involved_parties: Seattle Fire Department, Medic Unit 47, Paramedic Jennifer Ross, Officer James Wilson
Seattle Fire Department, Medic Unit 47, Paramedic Jennifer Ross, Officer James Wilson

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 09:31:22 AM, the Seattle Emergency Communications Center received a distress call leading to a priority response by the Seattle Fire Department and King County Medic Unit 47. First responders assessed Ms. Mitchell, who exhibited elevated blood pressure and acute cervical pain. Officer James Wilson and Officer Maria Gonzalez from the Seattle Police Department secured the scene and confirmed a traffic signal violation by Mr. Chen's vehicle through traffic loop data. No financial amounts were mentioned in the report.

metadata.involved_parties: Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez
Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 14:45:18, Ms. Sarah Mitchell was evaluated by Dr. Michael Patterson at Seattle Medical Center after being transported via King County Ambulance Service. She was diagnosed with a Grade 2 Whiplash Associated Disorder and a mild concussion. A CT scan confirmed no acute injuries. Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez conducted an interview with Mitchell, who provided dashcam footage related to the incident. The total medical invoice for the ER visit was $3,840.00.

metadata.involved_parties: Premier Auto Body Shop, Inspector Thomas Blake, Progressive Insurance
Premier Auto Body Shop, Inspector Thomas Blake, Progressive Insurance

__data__.text: On January 16, 2024, at 10:30 AM, a 2022 Honda Accord was inspected by Certified Inspector Thomas Blake at Premier Auto Body Shop following a transfer via flatbed tow truck. The inspection revealed critical unibody misalignment, including a 3.2-inch inward deformation of the driver's side A-pillar. The total repair estimate, certified by Independent Appraiser David Richardson, amounted to $23,102.50, which included $12,450.00 for OEM parts and $8,312.50 for labor.

metadata.involved_parties: Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Physical Therapist Amanda Chen
Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Physical Therapist Amanda Chen

__data__.text: On January 22, 2024, Ms. Mitchell attended a follow-up consultation with Dr. Patterson, who noted persistent cervical spine tenderness and significant limitations in range of motion. Dr. Patterson referred her for 12 sessions of physical therapy at Seattle Rehabilitation Center, focusing on cervical mobility and strengthening. Physical Therapist Amanda Chen conducted the intake session, where Mitchell scored 28/50 on the Neck Disability Index, indicating 'Moderate Disability'. No specific costs or financial amounts were mentioned in the report.

metadata.involved_parties: Marcus Thompson, Seattle Police, Traffic Engineer Dr. Susan Miller
Marcus Thompson, Seattle Police, Traffic Engineer Dr. Susan Miller

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 11:45 AM, an incident occurred involving Mr. Marcus Thompson, an eyewitness, and Dr. Susan Miller, a Senior Traffic Engineer from the Seattle Department of Transportation. Thompson reported that a Toyota, driven by Mr. Chen, ran a red light, corroborated by signal timing analysis showing a 2.277-second red light violation. The Seattle Police Department's video analysis confirmed this finding, establishing that Mr. Chen failed to yield the right of way, which was crucial for liability determination. No financial amounts were mentioned in the details provided.

metadata.involved_parties: Progressive Auto Insurance, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Finance Department
Progressive Auto Insurance, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Finance Department

__data__.text: On January 17, 2024, at 09:00 AM, Senior Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez finalized the financial reserving and payment schedule for Claim CLM-2024-00789-AUTO with Progressive Auto Insurance. The total claim value was certified at $47,850.00, which includes $44,010.00 for vehicle damage and $3,840.00 for medical expenses. All payments are scheduled for Electronic Funds Transfer, with the vehicle repair payment set for February 2, 2024. The total falls within the policy limits of $100,000.00 for property and $25,000.00 for medical.

metadata.involved_parties: Premier Auto Body Shop, Thomas Blake, Honda Parts Department
Premier Auto Body Shop, Thomas Blake, Honda Parts Department

__data__.text: On January 19, 2024, at 08:30:00, Premier Auto Body Shop's Service Coordinator Rebecca Sullivan initiated parts procurement for a 2022 Honda Accord. She placed an order with Honda Parts Distribution Center for 42 items valued at $12,450.00, utilizing expedited shipping due to a critical backorder on the Driver Side A-Pillar Reinforcement. Foreman Thomas Blake and Lead Technician Carlos Martinez prepared for the repair, establishing quality control checkpoints. Sullivan updated the customer, Ms. Mitchell, with a completion date of January 30, 2024.

metadata.involved_parties: Seattle Police, State Farm Insurance, Progressive Legal Department
Seattle Police, State Farm Insurance, Progressive Legal Department

__data__.text: On January 18, 2024, at 13:30:00, Seattle Police issued Traffic Citation TC-2024-0891 to Mr. Robert Chen for failing to obey a traffic control device. State Farm Insurance accepted 100% liability for the incident, waiving all comparative fault defenses, and confirmed responsibility for damages totaling $47,850, which includes $44,010 for vehicle property damage and $3,840 for medical expenses incurred by Sarah Mitchell. The investigation, led by Claims Representative Michael Torres, found clear evidence of Chen's fault based on traffic camera footage and witness statements.

metadata.involved_parties: Progressive Subrogation Department, State Farm Insurance, Finance Department
Progressive Subrogation Department, State Farm Insurance, Finance Department

__data__.text: On January 20, 2024, Progressive Auto Insurance's Subrogation Department, led by Specialist David Chen, initiated subrogation recovery procedures against State Farm Insurance to recover $48,350, which includes $47,850 in damages and a $500 deductible for claimant Mitchell. The demand package was sent via certified mail and electronically to State Farm's Subrogation Manager Robert Williams. State Farm acknowledged full liability on January 23, 2024, agreeing to issue payments of $40,000 by February 1, 2024, and $8,350 by February 15, 2024, ensuring Mitchell receives her deductible refund by February 5, 2024.

metadata.involved_parties: Premier Auto Body Shop, Progressive Insurance, Sarah Mitchell
Premier Auto Body Shop, Progressive Insurance, Sarah Mitchell

__data__.text: On January 30, 2024, at 14:00, Premier Auto Body completed the repair of Ms. Sarah Mitchell's 2022 Honda Accord, adhering to an 18-day timeline. Foreman Thomas Blake conducted a final quality assurance check, confirming structural integrity and a paint finish indistinguishable from factory standards. Progressive Field Inspector Monica Rodriguez validated the repairs and authorized final payment. Ms. Mitchell expressed satisfaction with the repairs and closed the rental invoice at $1,170.00, billed to Progressive.

__data__.text: Claim ID CLM-2024-00789-AUTO was closed on February 5, 2024, for policyholder Sarah Mitchell, involving a 2022 Honda Accord. The incident type was an auto accident, occurring on January 15, 2024. The total estimated claim value was $47,850.00, covering vehicle damage and medical expenses.
